          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Benefits</span><h2>Why Invest in Tax Free Bonds?</h2></div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>100% Tax-Free Interest</strong><p>Interest earned is completely exempt from income tax regardless of your tax slab. No TDS is deducted, and the income does not need to be included in your taxable income — a benefit unmatched by any other fixed-income product.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Superior Post-Tax Returns</strong><p>For investors in the 30% tax bracket, a 6% tax-free bond equals 8.57% pre-tax. Compare this with a bank FD at 7.5% which yields only 5.25% post-tax. The higher your tax slab, the more advantageous tax-free bonds become.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Government-Backed Safety</strong><p>Issued by PSUs with implicit or explicit government backing, tax-free bonds carry AAA ratings and near-sovereign credit quality. NHAI, REC, PFC, and IRFC are all Navratna or Maharatna companies with strong government support.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Listed & Tradeable</strong><p>All tax-free bonds are listed on NSE and BSE, providing liquidity to sell before maturity if needed. Active trading ensures transparent price discovery and reasonable bid-ask spreads for popular series.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Long-Term Wealth Preservation</strong><p>With tenures of 10–20 years, tax-free bonds are ideal for long-term goals like retirement planning. The combination of safe, tax-free income and capital preservation makes them a portfolio cornerstone.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>No Reinvestment Risk on Coupons</strong><p>Annual coupon payments provide reliable cash flows. Unlike cumulative instruments, you receive income every year, which can be used for expenses or reinvested in other opportunities at then-prevailing rates.</p></div></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

